photos.description:
Joan Chen
as Lu Mei

China’s tech titan of AI. Lu Mei built her AI company from the ground up with her husband. People assumed she was just the face, but after her husband passed away, it became clear she was the brains behind the operation.

Louis Cancelmi
as Todd

The head of Andy's security team. Todd may appear relaxed, but behind his calm demeanor lies a highly trained soldier who constantly scans rooms and situations for potential threats.

Jermaine Fowler
as Martin

While the other kids played outside, Martin watched movies — all sorts of movies. His own debut, made for next to nothing, had the references and rhythms of a master filmmaker.

Ryan J. Haddad
as Oliver

As a disabled child of immigrants, Oliver, formed a unique bond with a toy robot that mimicked his own gait. Oliver's fascination grew as he dismantled and explored the robot's mechanics, envisioning its potential in empowering and supporting disabled bodies.

Raúl Esparza
as David

An Argentinian-American venture capitalist and Andy’s number two, who, unlike Andy, grew up with money.

Edoardo Ballerini
as Ray

An AI built to do all the things no one has time to do anymore.

Javed Khan
as Rohan

A South Asian climatologist raised in England who developed a strong aversion towards humans and a firm belief that the escalating climate crisis would lead to the destruction of the natural world as we know it.

Pegah Ferydoni
as Ziba

An activist who escaped Iran by crossing the mountains by foot and found asylum in Berlin. She has spent all of her life fighting against the consolidation of wealth and power against the people.

Emma Corrin
as Darby Hart

A Gen Z amateur sleuth who grew up online and wields the hive mind of the internet to solve cold cases.

Clive Owen
as Andy Ronson

A college dropout with a dazzling mind who took his passion for gaming and programming to an AI security start-up and turned it into a multibillion-dollar sale.

Brit Marling
as Lee Andersen

A hacker who rode the early days of the internet into a kind of punk fame as a young woman who could code as well as the boys.

Alice Braga
as Sian

A Brazilian doctor who began her career working with astronauts and then trained and became one. Sian has the formidable distinction of being the first woman to walk on the moon.

Harris Dickinson
as Bill Farrah

Growing up in a struggling Ohio suburb with a single mother, he sought solace and connection through his online interactions, hacking, coding and solving puzzles.

movie_info.title: 世界尽头的一场谋杀
movie_info.original_title: A Murder at the End of the World
